reviews_data.review_text: Had a great time at the jazz night!!  What a great place--cant wait to go back!!
Marilyn made us the most delicious carrot cake for our wedding! Couldn't have asked for better ^-^

I was lucky enough to get to try three of the pound cakes available: Five Flavor, Chocolate, and Strawberry. *Absolutely* delicious!! These are old-fashioned pound cakes, dense in a good way, sweet and not over the top, and the icing is too good, especially on the chocolate. Do yourself a favor and stop by here! I can't wait to try some of the coconut cake.

reviews_data.review_text: Always a great experience!

For those that did not want to attend or could not for various reasons (I asked several folk) this joint here is a repeat...terrr!! Been knowing of this establishment for quite some time but finally getting here!
It's owner Marilyn and her hubby are making it work. And yall it's worth the $35. She can BAKE! Her desserts were scrumptious and succulent. I had the pistachio swirl nut cake. One dessert and unlimited beverages are available. Assortment of Tazo teas. Several coffee selections. Reg water or perrier, lemonade, tea. Extra dessert in house or to go are $5-6. No more than you pay at any other restaurant. I got to meet ladies my age. Fellowship and listen to some bomb jazz by "The Groove Master" $35...WHAT? I've paid x2 as much to hear jazz & got nothing to eat or drink w/ cost of ticket. Various artist play on select Sundays.  Support this Black couples business yall. It's a cute lil quaint and cozy joint. Feels like The Color Purple Harpos Juke Joint but on a 21st century scale...its clean, perfectly decorated. Nice and charming seating. Holds about 50 folk tops...so if u dislike crowds but u love jazz...this here is it!!!
#oh yea
#illbeback
Great coffee and dessert in a beautifully decorated place. Cakes, cookies and cobbler.
Phenomenal!!! The band, the hospitality and the desserts were all awesome!!! Can't wait to return! Marilyn and Sam are treasures with in the community!
Marilyn is the sweetest woman I ever met. And goodness can she bake! Highly recommend! Cute and cozy space!
Very nice cozy spot delicious pound cake
Every single item is amazing!
The cakes are awesome  .

A Wonderful Environment with The Best Desserts!!! Entertainment evenings are so relaxing and a phenomenal networking. I have never been disappointed at Heart 2 Heart. Wonderful Service, Exceeds all Expectations. The name said it All. Truly Heart 2 Heart.
Excellent venue. Desserts are super good. Music was fantastic! I recommend Heart 2 Heart to anyone who wants a relaxed atmosphere with great people.

We had a fantastic time. The Reggie Boule trio was great and the singer was a plus. I won't talk about the cake. Might I say you get a slice of your choice with the ticket price.
Marilynn and family are wonderful sponsors.
You will not regret attending a session.
We'll be back for the next session.
This place is a hidden gem. Hands down one of the best places to visit, whether you live in Charlotte or visiting. Everyone should know about this place.
Every cake and cookie I tasted was delicious. The ambience of the bakery and pleasing personality of the proprietor Marilyn is "over the top".
I had a piece of the chocolate cake. It was delicious. The prices however will keep me from making this my go to bakery. Very expensive. I'm sad.
A wonderful place to unwind and have coffee, tea,and desserts check her out
Great cakes and exceptional service. Sunshine delight is my favorite cake. Best cakes in a hundred miles.
the service is great
One trip to heart 2 heart and you'll fall in love with the cakes and the owner.  Sunshine delight is #1 in my book.
Great place loving ppl
Great atmosphere! The food was so good and service was exceptional.
